reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Looks more expensive
reviews.reviewText: I really like the color of the gold finish. The chain is a nice mid weight. This is one of two necklaces I take when I travel. This works well with simple dresses as well as with shorts or jeans and tees. The chain adjusts enough to make it wearable with different necklines. Very comfortable. It's low cost means I won't be devasted if I lose it. I like that the back side of the pendant has a design so it can be flipped either way. Great, little necklace worn with simple hoop earrings for a clean, contemporary look. I'm in my 70's and try to stay current with my style without pushing it to the crazy lady level. This simple necklace strikes a good balance. I can mix this with pricier pieces and it holds its own. I like mine so much, I've purchased another as a gift. Definitely a good find. I've not worn it in the shower or the pool so I can't vouch for it under those conditions but I've worn it a fair bit and it still looks new. At this price, I'll just get another if it starts to show wear.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So Far So Good!
reviews.reviewText: I received my necklace on January 2nd and today is January 13th and I have had zero issues with this necklace! None. I take it off before bed and I only wear it when I’m leaving the house. If you’re looking for something you can wear forever and never take off, this isn’t it. It’s plated metal, so it’s not meant to last forever. It is however, a gorgeous, expensive-looking necklace! It really does look like 10K gold. It’s not a dark brassy gold that looks so obviously fake whatsoever! It’s not a super lightweight chain either. It has a nice weight to it without it being heavy or bulky feeling. I mean, this necklace would fool me if I saw someone casually wearing it around and I’m a trained lapidary artist (I cut gemstones and make jewelry)! I really like that it’s 100% reversible! The heart on the back is super cute and a nice touch. It’ll be great for Valentine’s Day if that’s your thing. I’ve worn this necklace every day for the last 10 days and so far so good! No rash or turning green. I had even forgotten that I was wearing it when I sprayed perfume on me. I did immediately take a dry microfiber cloth and wipe it off and that saved it I think. I also recommend doing this after each wear anyways. It’ll keep the necklace clean and prolong the life of your necklace as well. There is a little care tip card that comes with it that says to basically not move at all or you’ll ruin it lol. I promise, if you’re gentle it’ll last! This is NOT a paid review. I purchased this necklace with my OWN money, straight from Amazon. This review is for those whom, like myself, rely heavily on others’ reviews of products prior to buying them. Happy shopping!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Decent quality for the price
reviews.reviewText: I actually purchased this necklace in two different letters (both gold) and it actually came out nicer than expected. The quality is good, I haven’t experienced any irritation from the necklace so far. I do remove it nightly and try to avoid lotions, and sprays as the directions recommend. I also store it in my closet away from the moisture of my bathroom and so far she’s still shining and looking good as new! I think this is great for a gift or even something nice for yourself.

reviews.reviewText: This is a very pretty necklace. I first saw it on a family member and truly believed it was pure gold! I commented how pretty it is, and she sent me the link. I cannot believe the beautiful necklace is this reasonably priced! It’s shiny, pretty, love it! I am careful with my jewelry and I never wear my jewelry around water, so I can’t attest to how it would withstand that, but I think I’d steer clear of wearing it in water just to be safe.
